parameters:
Manager: In business, we talk across the desk.
It's common sense.

Manager: Our members' ranks change based on their
transaction frequency.

Manager: Our regular customers are mostly in the
highest rank. The highest rank is called 'Family'.

(I just walked in, but I wonder what kind of shop
this is...?)

Manager: Customer...! Do you have something good?
Will you sell it here?
Sell...? Is this place a pawn shop?

Manager: We introduce people who want something to
those who have it. The same goes the other way
around.

(I wonder if this is a place that introduces and
mediates people who want to buy and sell things
privately?)

(It seems like this kind of place would have
people bringing in hidden treasures, it looks
interesting)

Manager: If you'd like, would you like to become a
member?

Huh, then... should I register...? By the way, is
there an annual fee or something...?

Manager: If you register as a seller, there won't
be an annual fee. However, in return, you must
sell something a few times without fail.

(...Speaking of which, I came across quite a few
things that I don't need while cleaning up after
moving...)

Manager: Alright, then let's go with the photos.
Smile~

Manager: ...Okay then. From today onwards, you'll
be our seller.

Manager: And also, you need to decide on a handle
name that you will use during transactions.

(Hmm, I can't think of anything catchy... Maybe
I'll just change the pronunciation.)

Manager: Okay then, Ryoko. Let's go with the
explanation...

Manager: The buyer came earlier than expected!
Alright, 'Ryoko', let's go to that room over
there!

...? Um, right now, I don't have anything with
me...

Manager: Don't worry. The buyer is a kind person
and will teach you various things! Just listen to
what they say and it'll be okay!

Manager: You'll understand once you give it a try!
Head over to that room and wait!

Manager: Ryoko! How are you? The buyer is already
here, so please take care of it!

(I have to sell another weird one... What should I
do...)

Manager: What the hell!? This is a lifelong
request!! Don't keep the buyer waiting any
longer!!

This event requires a lewdness level of 20 or
higher.

Manager: Ryoko! How is your body feeling? The
customer specifically requested you, so please
take care of it!

(I have a bad feeling about this... What should I
do...?)

Manager: Wha-?! For a lifetime!! No, even for the
sake of my grandchildren's request!!

This event requires a lewdness level of 50 or
higher.
Store Manager: See you next time, okay?

Manager: Ryoko! Today's customers are regular
ones, so feel at ease when conducting
transactions!

(...I don't really trust her, but I'm curious
about what she means by regular... Maybe I should
go ahead and conduct the transaction.)
I won't go to the transaction room

Manager: Well, can you do me a favor and say
that?... Will you do it for me?

This event requires a lewdness level of 80 or
higher.

This event requires a lewdness level of 230 or
higher.

Manager: Ayako's reputation is skyrocketing! And
today is a gratitude festival! It's a great
opportunity to earn money with lots of people
gathering!

(So many people gathering...? Ah... I wonder what
will be done to me...♡)
I won't go to the negotiation room

Manager: By any chance, will you do such a thing
for me...? Will you do it?

This event requires a lewdness level of 80 or
higher.

Manager: We made quite a profit, so let's take a
break for a while! I'm going on vacation!
